    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-22T14:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-22T14:45:00-05:00" n="866"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/7632: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-22T14:00:00-05:45"
                            >November 22, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 23—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>217. Department’s telegram 118, November 16, 1 p.m.; and my despatch 969,
                    November 16, first enclosure. National and Legal Governing Boards of the Liberal
                    and Conservative Parties met together November 19 and appointed a commission
                    representing the two parties to confer with President-elect <persName
                        corresp="#p_SJB2">Sacasa</persName> and reach an agreement with him
                    concerning the procedure to be followed in the common endeavor of the parties to
                    effect the pacification of Nicaragua under agreement No. 1.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HME1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
